,"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2","NA",{"_":51,"notBefore":52,"notAfter":53,"precision":54},"A date in the period 4th — 1st century BCE seems most likely, but it is impossible to be certain in the absence of further information",-400,-1,"low",[56,59],{"_":2,"type":57,"ref":58},"ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462313",{"_":2,"type":60,"ref":61},"modern","http://sws.geonames.org/11103527",[63],[64,65],37.69904,14.808181,"Italy","Sicily","unknown",{"_":70,"mainLang":71,"languages":72},"Ancient Greek","grc",[70],{"n":74,"url":75,"height":76,"width":77,"desc":78,"surfaceType":79},"screen","ISic001388_tiled.tif","115px","945px","Drawing of P.Orsi, RSA 1900, p.43 no.2","front",[],[82,83,84,85,86,87,88,89,90],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Orsi, 1900, Frammenti epigrafici sicelioti","Albanese, 1991, Mendolito","Castelli, 1769, Siciliae et objacentium insularum veterum inscriptionum nova collectio","Castelli, 1784, Siciliae et objacentium insularum veterum inscriptionum nova collectio prolegomenis et notis illustrata, et iterum cum emendationibus, & auctariis evulgata","Franz, 1853, CIG","Russo, 1911, Illustrazione storico-archeologica di Adernò","Manganaro, 1961, Iscrizioni di Adrano","Prag, 2015, Epigrafia",[92,93,94,95,96,97,98,99,100],"Q2SBPG9F","UE3VRJA7","IVAU3I2N","SPTB56H3","7PSFHSUH","TQMVHEVL","CRSSWMDV","6V679NMW","SHKXSQLC",[102,103,104,13,105,26,106,106,107,108,68,109,71],"isic001388","greek dedication to herakles",{"_":10},"altar","mendolito","italy","sicily","ancient greek","Text encoding: Jonathan Prag, edition source:",{"file":112,"uri":112,"title":113,"status":114,"editionAuthor":11,"type":115,"objectType":119,"material":123,"condition":29,"layoutDesc":127,"handNote":131,"date":139,"places":143,"geo":151,"country":66,"region":67,"settlement":149,"repository":29,"textLang":155,"facsimile":157,"provenance":145,"letterHeights":162,"publications":163,"zotero":174,"keywords":185,"html":110},"ISic001391","Greek inscription recording enjoyment of a spring",{"_":10},{"_":116,"ana":117,"ref":118},"touristic text","#function.touristic","https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/135.html",{"_":120,"ana":121,"ref":122},"rock face","#object.rock-face","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/211",{"_":124,"ana":125,"ref":126},"stone","#material.stone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html",{"layout":128},{"p":129,"rs":130,"damage":29},"The text maintains a clear left margin, laid out over three lines. The extended spacing in lines 1 and 2 has sometimes suggested to editors that the text divides into columns; however this is probably to compensate for the fact that lines 2 and 3 are shortened by the insertion of a large engraved palm leaf (20 cm high) on the right margin.",{"_":34,"ana":35,"ref":36},{"lettering":132,"dimensions":133},"The text is engraved in large bold letters, with the topmost stroke often extended vertically above the letter on Α, Λ, Δ. Letter forms are somewhat variable within the inscription, with lunate and straight sigma used indiscriminately; epsilon is normally straight, but appears lunate in ΦΗϹΕΙΝΟϹ in line 2; alpha is normally straight but displays broken bar in ΕΥΦΡΑΝΘΗΣΑΝ in line 3; phi has an angular eye in lines 1 and 2 but a rounded eye in line 3; variation within texts is however common, and it is not necessary to assume that this reflects different hands in use within the text. Ligatures are employed several times in the text, which has been the source of several confused readings in the past.",[134,138],{"type":41,"l":135,"from":43,"to":136,"h":137,"unit":44},"Line 1-3","line3","70-90",{"type":46,"l":47,"from":43,"to":48,"unit":44},{"_":140,"notBefore":141,"notAfter":142,"precision":54},"3rd century CE or early 4th century CE (Manganaro)",201,350,[144,148],{"_":145,"type":57,"ref":146,"corresp":147},"Adranon","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462074","#findspot",{"_":149,"type":60,"ref":150},"Adrano","http://sws.geonames.org/2525769",[152],[153,154],37.66358,14.83283,{"_":70,"mainLang":71,"languages":156},[70],{"n":74,"url":158,"height":159,"width":160,"desc":161,"surfaceType":79},"ISic001391_tiled.tif","2388px","3716px","Photo J. Prag",[],[82,164,165,166,167,87,88,83,168,169,89,170,171,84,172,173,85,86,90],"Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Bulletin épigraphique, 1888-","Pirro, 1733, Sicilia sacra disquisitionibus, et notitiis illustrata. ... Editio tertia, emendata, & continuatione aucta cura, et studio ... Antonini Mongitore","Amico, 1757-1760, Lexicon topographicum Siculum","Schmoll, 1958, Die vorgriechischen Sprachen siziliens","Soraci, 1958, Appunti di epigrafia greca e romana relativa alla regione hyblense-inessea-adranita","Ferrua, 1989, Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia","Manganaro, 1992, Iscrizioni \"rupestri\" di Sicilia","Libertini, 1932, Adranon. Questioni storiche e topografiche","Gualtherus, 1624 [1625], Siciliæ obiacentium insular. et Bruttiorum antiquæ tabulæ, cum animadversionib",[92,175,176,177,178,97,98,93,179,180,99,181,182,94,183,184,95,96,100],"F2GG87EQ","77P5MNIR","ZCCYR8S7","YZEYESTP","JQNCGI8C","ZXGG3V8Z","759ZXHKQ","UQRFDXEG","ICCT8RK8","ZP8DE8KS",[186,187,188,116,120,124,189,190,107,108,190,109,71],"isic001391","greek inscription recording enjoyment of a spring",{"_":10},"adranon","adrano",{"file":192,"uri":192,"title":193,"status":194,"editionAuthor":11,"type":195,"objectType":196,"material":199,"condition":203,"layoutDesc":205,"handNote":211,"date":350,"places":355,"geo":358,"country":66,"region":67,"settlement":149,"repository":360,"idno":364,"textLang":367,"facsimile":369,"provenance":145,"letterHeights":374,"publications":375,"zotero":379,"keywords":383,"html":110},"ISic002995","Inscribed altar or statue base",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":197,"ana":18,"ref":19,"certainty":198},"altar\n                                    ",{"locus":21,"match":22,"assertedValue":23,"desc":24},{"_":200,"ana":201,"ref":202},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":204},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":206},{"p":207,"rs":208,"damage":209},"The inscribed face is maximum 0.26 m high and 0.497 m wide. The text is extremely irregular and uneven in its layout, with letters of varying size and the horizontal of the lines very erratic. The text appears to observe the left margin with some consistency, but is extremely irregular on the right. The full height of the face is employed: the final line is squeezed.",{"_":34,"ana":35,"ref":36},{"ana":210},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":212,"dimensions":310},[213,214],"The inscription is crudely engraved and inexpertly laid out on the face. The letter forms are primarily distinguished by their irregularity and the poor quality of the engraving. Theta is formed by large circle with single mid-dot; epsilon on occasion has a shorter middle bar; omega is notable in being consistently extremely open, with short horizontal tails (projecting outwards only); omicron is generally full-size, or nearly so, but also smaller; kappa has equal length arms which join the vertical, but do not generally extend fully to the top/bottom of the line; alpha is broad with straight bar; phi has a rounded closed eye; nu on occasion has a shorter right vertical, leaning outwards; sigma is either four straight bars (with top and bottom strokes open beyond the horizontal) or with the top and bottom strokes joined by a single curving stroke; rho is closed, with either a rounded or an angular eye; pi has a shorter right hasta; mu is in one case faint and compressed, in the other broad and composed of four short off vertical strokes; delta is either regular, or with the base line angled down to the right.",{"_":215,"ref":216},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                        